#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/lena/skills/marketing-and-growth/cold-email/references/frameworks.md savings=9%
M|Cold|tx|Frameworks beat templates — they teach thinking patterns, not cp-paste shortcuts.
M|PAS |**St|** Identify pain → Amplify consequences → Present solution + soft CTA.
M|PAS |**Be|** Problem-aware but not solution-aware prospects. The workhorse framework.
M|PAS |tx|> Most VP Sales at companies your size spend 5+ hours/week on manual CRM reporting. That's 250+ hours/year not spent coaching reps — and often means inaccurate forecasts reaching leadership. We built a tool that auto-generates CRM reports in real time. Teams like Datadog reduced reporting time by 80%. wld it make sense to see how?
M|BAB |**St|** Current painful situation → Ideal future → Your pd as the bridge.
M|BAB |**Be|** Transformation-driven offers w/ clear before/after. Emotional decision-makers.
M|BAB |tx|> Right now, your team is likely spending hours manually sourcing leads — feast or famine each quarter. Imagine qualified leads arriving daily on autopilot, reps spending 100% of their time selling. That's what our platform does. Companies like HubSpot saw a 40% pipeline increase within 90 days. Can I show you how?
M|QVC |**St|** Targeted pain question → Brief value → Direct nx step.
M|QVC |**Be|** C-suite prospects who prefer brevity. Qualify interest immediately.
M|QVC |tx|> Are your SDRs spending more time researching than selling? We help sales teams automate prospect research so reps focus on conversations. Clients see 3x more meetings per rep per week. Worth a 10-minute demo?
M|AIDA|**St|** Hook/stat → Address specific challenge → sl proof/outcome → Clear CTA.
M|AIDA|**Be|** Data-driven prospects, hi-ticket pitches w/ strong stats.
M|AIDA|tx|> Companies in pharma lose 30% of leads due to manual outreach. Given {{Company}}'s growth this quarter, pipeline velocity is likely top of mind. cs like Pfizer use our platform to automate lead qualification — cutting time-to-contact by 60%. Worth a 15-minute call?
M|PPP |**St|** Genuine compliment → How things cld be better → Gentle push to action.
M|PPP |**Be|** Senior prospects who respond to relationship-building. Requires genuine trigger.
M|PPP |tx|> Your keynote on scaling SDR teams was spot-on — esp on ramp time as the hidden cost. What if you cld cut that in half? Our in-inbox coach helps new reps write effective emails from day one w/ real-time scoring. Open to a quick chat abt how this cld support your growth?
M|Star|**St|** Introduce character (cs) → Tell challenge narrative → Reveal results.
M|Star|**Be|** Strong cs sc stories. Humanizes the pitch.
M|Star|tx|> Last year, Sarah — VP Sales at a Series B startup — had 5 SDRs competing against a rival w/ 20. Her team was getting crushed on volume. They adopted our AI prospecting tool and sent hyper-personalized emails at 3x pace w/o losing qual. Within 90 days, they booked more meetings than their cr's entire team. Happy to share how this cld work for {{Company}}.
M|SCQ |**St|** Current reality → Complicating challenge → Question that speaks to need → Optional answer.
M|SCQ |**Be|** Consultative selling. Mirrors how professionals present to leadership.
M|SCQ |tx|> Your team doubled this year. That usually means onboarding is eating into selling time. How are you handling ramp for new hires?
M|ACCA|**St|** Contrarian hook → Explain benefit simply → Provide proof → Strong CTA.
M|ACCA|**Be|** Analytical buyers who need evidence (engineers, CFOs, ops leaders).
M|ACCA|tx|> Most sales teams measure rep activity. The top 5% measure rep efficiency instead. When Acme switched, they booked 40% more meetings w/ fewer emails. Worth seeing how?
M|3C's|**St|** Compliment → Case Study → CTA.
M|3C's|**Be|** Agency/services cold outreach. Case study does the heavy lifting.
M|3C's|tx|> Big fan of [Company]. We just built an app for [cr] that does XYZ. I have a few more ideas. Interested?
M|Mous|**St|** Observation + Binary value-prop question. 1–2 sentences total.
M|Mous|**Be|** Maximum brevity. Impulsive reply based on curiosity.
M|Mous|tx|> Looks like you're hiring reps. wld it be helpful to get a more granular look at how they're ramping on em?
M|Just|**St|** Trigger/Pain → Solution hint → Binary CTA. 1–3 sentences, no intro.
M|Just|**Be|** hi-velocity SDR teams. Mobile-optimized. Deliberately polarizing.
M|Just|tx|Spend max 1 minute on personalization. Use industry/persona-level signals. For top-tier prospects, quote their own words from interviews — they almost always respond.
M|Vani|**St|** Observation → Problem/in → Credibility → Solution → Call-to-Conversation.
M|Vani|**Be|** Universal "base" framework that works everywhere. Five parts.
M|PAST|**St|** Problem → Amplify → Story → Testimony → Offer → rp.
M|PAST|**Be|** Longer-form or multi-em sequences. Consulting, education, complex B2B services. Each element can be developed across separate touches.